title: ‘Things could spiral out of control’: US shoots down Iranian drone as tensions escalate
description: The Australian columnist Tom Switzer discusses tensions between America and Iran after the US military shot down an Iranian drone approaching an aircraft carrier.  “All it requires is an accident or a miscalculation, and things could spiral out of control,” Mr Switzer told Sky News host Chris Kenny.  “My sense is the president wants to show force, to intimidate the Mullahs.”

title: Bill and Hillary Clinton agree to testify in US Congress
description: Sky News host Danica De Giorgio says Bill and Hillary Clinton have agreed to testify in US Congress.

title: Bill Gates rebukes allegations of STD in Epstein files
description: Sky News host Danica De Giorgio says billionaire Bill Gates has rebuked the details alleged in the Epstein files of him contracting a sexually transmitted disease and sought to give his wife antibiotics.

title: The police publicly admit they can’t guarantee safety
description: Shadow Education Minister Julian Lesser criticises the police for admitting publicly that they cannot guarantee safety.  “I don’t want to see the Jewish community retraumatised after what it’s gone through at Bondi,” Mr Lesser told Sky News host Sharri Markson.   “To the police, I say your job is not just to protect the peace, but it’s to protect the peaceful.  “We have to be able to have gatherings.”

title: Michele Bullock under fire for interest rate hike
description: Former Treasury assistant secretary David Pearl expressed anger over the Reserve Bank of Australia's (RBA) interest rate hike.  Mr Pearl criticised the lack of contrition from RBA Governor Michele Bullock.

title: ‘Flabbergasted’: Teal MP’s ‘completely out of touch’ question
description: Shadow Education Minister Julian Lesser slams Teal MP for ridiculous statement during question time.   “I was flabbergasted by this question,” Mr Lesser told Sky News host Sharri Markson.  “The teals are completely out of touch here.”

title: Albanese causing household finances to ‘crumble’ amid non-functional opposition
description: Sky News host Sharri Markson says without a functioning opposition government to hold Prime Minister Anthony Albanese to account, Australia’s economy and household finances are “crumbling”.   “Around the world, inflation is mostly no longer a problem, and interest rates are falling. Households are feeling relief in most comparable developed nations,” Ms Markson said.  “But without a functioning opposition to hold the Albanese Government to account, our economy and household finances are crumbling.”

title: Andrew Hastie spotted in parliament with Sun Tzu’s The Art of War
description: Sky News host Freya Leach says Liberal MP Andrew Hastie was spotted sitting in parliament with Sun Tzu’s The Art of War.   “Andrew Hastie … he was spotted sitting on the very back bench of parliament reading a copy of Sun Tzu’s The Art of War,” Ms Leach said.  “Next to him was one of his allies, Garth Hamilton, who was reading Shakespeare's Othello.”

title: ‘Party full of w**kers’: Clive Palmer hits out against Liberal Party
description: Sky News host Freya Leach comments on today’s parliamentary intervention from Clive Palmer.    “There was a surprising intervention today from Clive Palmer, who’s said behind the scenes he’s been talking with individual members of the National Party about its future direction,” Ms Leach said.   “He did not mince his words.”

title: Activists hijack street art campaign with images of man charged with terrorism in Bondi massacre
description: Sky News host Peta Credlin says activists hijacking street art with images of the man charged with the Bondi terror attack is “disgusting”.  “Action on the streets of Melbourne where activists have hijacked a street art campaign and they’ve plastered the city of Melbourne with images of the man charged by police with terrorism over the Bondi events,” Ms Credlin said.  Melbourne Deputy Lord Mayor Roshena Campbell joined Ms Credlin to discuss the consequences around the posters.

title: Greens Councillor thinks ‘vandals shouldn’t pay for damage if the monument was unpopular’
description: Sky News host James Macpherson criticises Greens Councillor Olivia Ball for voting against a crackdown on vandals.  “City of Melbourne councillors voted this week to crack down on people who vandalise historic monuments, agreeing that if you damage a monument, you pay for it.  “Greens Councillor Olivia Ball voted against the motion, arguing that damage to monuments should be considered on a case-by-case basis.  “Vandals wouldn't need to pay for damage if it were agreed the monument was already unpopular.  “She was promoting a protest on the steps of State Parliament at which the steps of Parliament were vandalised with the phrase globalise the intifada"

title: ‘People are doing it tough’: 13th rate rise under this government
description: Shadow Attorney General Andrew Wallace criticises the Australian government for yet another rate rise.   “I think what Australians are seeing is a government that is absolutely full of hubris,” Mr Wallace told Sky News host Danica DeGiorgio.  “Australians can see that the government is not focused on them.  “People are really doing it tough; we’ve seen the 13th interest rate rise under this government.”

title: ‘Not great’: Looking ‘terrible’ for Republicans ahead of US midterms
description: 'The Megyn Kelly Show' host Megyn Kelly says it’s looking “terrible” for Republicans ahead of the US midterms.   “Right now, I think it’s looking terrible for Republicans in the midterm,” Ms Kelly told Sky News host Paul Murray.  “It’s not great … I think the Democrats will easily win the House in the midterm election.”

title: Megyn Kelly blasts Billie Eilish claiming she looked like a ‘piano’ at 2026 Grammys
description: 'The Megyn Kelly Show' host Megyn Kelly says Billie Eilish looked like a “piano” at the 2026 Grammys.   “Billie Eilish … she looked like a piano,” Ms Kelly told Sky News host Paul Murray.  “Stiff, weird angles, she never looks good.”

title: ‘Privileged out-of-touch elite jerks’ attempt to lecture public at Grammys: Megyn Kelly
description: 'The Megyn Kelly Show' host Megyn Kelly blasts Hollywood celebrities for having the nerve to “lecture the rest of us on how we need to live.”  “It’s amazing to me, to watch these rich privileged out of-touch elite jerks stand up there and try to lecture the rest of us on how we need to live,” Ms Kelly told Sky News host Paul Murray.  “Each one of whom … lives in a guarded estate and will never have to deal with the consequences of an illegal immigrant in their lives.”
